                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="a78e-ed35-c409-5cda">Unwieldy</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Aquila Imperialis" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="b37e-5d3b-dad7-4608">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">Instead of rolling for it, the model and the attached unit can automatically pass a Leadership test once per game. Unique</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Armorium cherub" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="10d3-1978-3ef3-422f">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model or the attached unit can fire a weapon twice during one activation. Each unit can benefit from this effect only once per round. Ammo(1).</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Auspex scanner" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="478d-93b5-9e5b-4bf4">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">If the unit has not already activated this turn, it may immediately use up its order and fire at an enemy unit within 18" that is deployed as reinforcement as if it had been given the "Stand & Shoot" order. The attack resolves after the enemy unit has been deployed and before it takes another action.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Auxiliary grenade launcher" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="7c0e-2c23-569c-46e6">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">All grenades of the model have four times the range.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Bionics" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="e785-c2c1-a8b4-43cc">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model receives a 6+ invulnerability save.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Book of Malcador" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="fc06-8b27-ac51-4536">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model knows one more psychic power from any psychic discipline it normally has access to. Unique. Only for Librarians.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Chapter banner" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="b0aa-ae5a-0ad7-46fa">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The unit gains a bonus of +1 to Leadership and Combat resolutions. As long as the banner bearer is alive, Mission objectives that are held by this unit can not be contested by enemy units. Additionally, all models in the unot gain +1 Attack. Unique. Only for Ancients.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Familiar" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="e3f5-4da2-1972-4117">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model may sacrifice the Familiar to reroll a psychic power manifestation test. While it is alive, the model gains +1 Initiative. Only for Librarians.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Gravis armor" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="46b4-f651-a4fe-44ef">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains +1 Toughness, the "Warded" ability and the special rules "Massive(1)" and "Unyielding". Not combinable with other armors.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Iron halo" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="1c13-4057-9856-4518">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains a 4+ invulnerability save.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Jump pack infantry" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="fab7-8e3a-c479-4810">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains +6" movement and the "Jump pack infantry" rule. Only for infantry.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Marksman honours" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="5c60-c125-bd60-48de">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains +1 Ballistic Skill.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Master-crafted armor" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="07d5-ce8f-42ff-4940">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains a 2+ armor save. Not combinable with other armors.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Master-crafted weapon" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="067c-4ecf-e552-45f9">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">One weapon of the model gains the ability "Master-crafted".</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Omniscope" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="66dd-e8fa-2b5d-4670">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The bearer and their attached unit gain the "Seeking" ability against enemy units within 12".</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Parry shield" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="0542-dccc-2657-4c86">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains the ability "Parry".</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Phobos armor" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="95ed-e0df-f09a-449e">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains the abilities "Move Through Cover" and "Infiltrator." Not combinable with other armors.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Purity seal" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="37db-7dd8-dcf3-4dd5">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">Enemy Psykers suffer -1 to their psychic tests when the psychic power of this model or the attached unit targets them directly.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Psychic training" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="1e41-f014-356d-4fec">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model knows one additional psychic power from one of their chosen psychic disciplines. If it already knows all powers from each discipline, it may instead learn one power from a new discipline it has access to. Can be taken multiple times.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Refractor field" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="c8d0-9b2b-446a-471f">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains a 5+ invulnerability save.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Relic of the chapter" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="fdda-2712-66bd-463f">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">One weapon of the model gains one of the following:
- Additional +6" Range (only for ranged weapons)
- Additional +1 Strength
- Additional -1 AP
- Additional +1 AT
Every enhancement is unique per army.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Selfless healer" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="bc7e-09a2-6bb6-4fc2">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">At the end of its movement, the model can attempt to heal a creature within 3". On a 4+, a model regains up to 1 lost Wound. Only for Apothecaries. Unique.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Signum" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="fcff-3f12-79c5-4fba">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">Instead of using their own ranged weapons, the model may grant a friendly creature model within 6" range +1 to hit rolls this round.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Space Marine bike" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="918e-3a28-9042-4976">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains +6" movement, +1 Toughness, +1 Wound, a Twin bolt rifle, the "Bike" type, and "Devastating Charge" (see Outrider Squads). Only for infantry.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Storm shield" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="cc5e-9bdb-c532-4a26">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains the abilities "Deflect" and "Parry". Only for Infantry and Jump pack infantry units.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Swordsman honours" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="dcf7-f413-343a-4c94">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains +1 Weapon skill.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Teleport homing beacon" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="2a77-620f-0902-4b21">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">A friendly unit arriving within 3" of the bearer via Deep strike does not scatter. The Teleport homer must be present on the table at the beginning of the battle round in order to be used.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Terminator armor" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="59c7-e134-e2cc-43d3">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">The model gains +1 Toughness, +1 Attack, 2+ armor save, 5+ invulnerable save, and the abilities "Massive(1)", "Deep strike" and "Unyielding." Only for infantry. Not combinable with other armors.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
        <profile name="Trophy" typeId="03e4-280e-70a0-4395" typeName="Equipment" hidden="false" id="dde9-75e9-e202-487a">
            <characteristics>
                <characteristic name="Keywords" typeId="0207-88db-7926-4ba6">Enemy units within a 6" radius suffer -1 to their morale value.</characteristic>
            </characteristics>
        </profile>
